  "texts": [
    "We can find said intermediary services grouped into the following categories:• Mere conduit intermediaries: These entities merely provide transmission of information over the internet, such as broadband providers, web hosting services, and WiFi hotspot operators.",
    "They are exempted from broad [182] Information that is false and deliberately created to harm a person, social group, organization or country 2018 High-Level Expert Group (HLEG) final report [35] All forms of false, inaccurate, or misleading information designed, presented, and promoted to intentionally cause public harm or for profit 2018 Code of Practice on Disinformation, Action Plan against Disinformation [48] Verifiably false or misleading information that is created, presented, and disseminated for economic gain or to intentionally deceive the public, and may cause public harm 2020 European Democracy Action Plan [53] Disinformation is false or misleading content that is spread with an intention to deceive or secure economic or political gain and which may cause public harm 2021 Guidance on Strengthening the Code of Practice [47] The different phenomena to be addressed, while clearly acknowledging the important differences between them.",
    "Disinformation in this sense includes disinformation in the narrow sense, misinformation, as well as information influence operations and foreign interference in the information space, including from foreign actors, where information manipulation is used with the effect of causing significant public harm 2022 Strengthened Code of Practice on Disinformation [49] Adopts the definition of the European Democracy Action Plan liability under Article 3 and have minimal transparency duties under Article 13.",
    "This reflects their technical role in simply transporting data packets across networks without knowledge of content.• Caching intermediaries: Entities that provide transient storage and transmission of information for the sole purpose of enhancing efficiency in onward transmission.Common examples are content delivery networks (CDNs) that cache content to reduce latency.",
    "Caching intermediaries benefit from liability exemptions under Article 4 but must expeditiously remove or disable access to cached illegal content upon obtaining knowledge of its illegal nature based on Articles 5 and 14."
  ],
